<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="M" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Manhood" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Manhood,</orth> 1) virility, opposed to womanhood: <cit><quote>fit you to your m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. cym 3.4.195" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. III, 4, 195</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) virility, opposed to boyhood: <cit><quote>thy prime of m. daring,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.170" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 IV, 4, 170</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>many unrough youths that even now protest their first of m.</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 5.2.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. V, 2, 11</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) qualities becoming a man, bravery, fortitude, honour: <bibl n="shak. ado 4.1.321" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado IV, 1, 321</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.412" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 412</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.198" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 4, 198</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.2.155" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 2, 155</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.141" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 141</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.4.141" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 141</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 2.1.103" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 1, 103</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.2.53" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 53</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.3.66" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 3, 66</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 5.2.75" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B V, 2, 75</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.2.108" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 2, 108</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.2.108" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 2, 108</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.2.20" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 20</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 1.2.276" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 2, 276</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 2.2.47" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.1.246" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. III, 1, 246</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.14" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 3.1.103" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 1, 103</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.4.319" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 4, 319</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.2.68" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 68</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.153" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 153</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.10.23" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 10, 23</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.2.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 2, 2</bibl>. Mrs. Quickly and Fluellen agree in saying <emph>saving your m.</emph> for <emph>saving your honour,</emph> or <cit><quote>your reverence:</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.1.29" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 1, 29</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. h5 4.8.36" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 IV, 8, 36</bibl>.
